author: stefan2
msg: Introduce the concepts of "entry keys" to address cache entries and "full
keys" to actually identify a given item.
This commit only introduces the respective struct definitions and replaces
the plain array we used previously for keys.  Lots of code churn but no
actual data format or logic change.
(entry_key_t): Replace array with a struct - to be extended later.
(full_key_t): New type - to be extended later.
(get_group_index): Pass in the key as explicit pointer and update to
(find_entry): Now expect a full key for the lookup.
membuffer_cache_set_partial): Always use the full key for lookup.
(svn_membuffer_cache_t): Use the complete keys instead of folded ones.
